(classify_bash_cmd) defaults to BashCmdKind::Other [2]. This routes the output
through infer_lang_from_bash, which detects the target file's extension, loads
the appropriate language grammar, and runs the entire file output through
Syntect to produce beautifully highlighted code blocks [2].

